## Agent checklist

- [ ] Do normal and large text meet **4.5:1** / **3:1** on their real backgrounds (including states)?
- [ ] Do control borders, informative icons, and visible focus meet **≥ 3:1** where required?
- [ ] Does **`<html lang>`** stay correct for locale routes (middleware header + root layout), not only an inner `lang` wrapper?
- [ ] Do **links and icon controls** have a **discernible name** at every breakpoint where they are focusable (**`aria-label`** from dictionaries when text is hidden or icon-only)?
- [ ] Do states **avoid color-only** signaling (text/icon/pattern backup)?
- [ ] Are **semantic token pairs** used instead of ad hoc combinations?
- [ ] Were **dark mode** or **new surfaces** reviewed for contrast?
- [ ] On **dark footers / legal one-liners**, avoid **very low `text-white/xx` opacity** for small type without verifying ratio (prefer verified neutrals or measured tokens)?
- [ ] Did Lighthouse Accessibility (or equivalent) on the touched screen show **no new** contrast/focus/link-name/`html`-lang regressions?
- [ ] When several tenant URLs must ship: were **multi-URL Lighthouse** smokes run or scheduled per **`docs/runbooks/accessibility-multi-tenant.md`** (where applicable)?
